        Returns:
        true, if these variants do not depend on attribute values.

      • getImage

        public Tileset.VarImage getImage()
        Get the default variant. For attribute independent variants, the default variant is determined by the defaultName field, if present. If this field is empty, the default variant is the one, that is named like the parent kind. In case of attribute dependency, the default variant is defined by the attributes default values.
        Returns:
        The default variant.
